-- Austria's Volksbanken sells Romanian unit to Banca Transilvania
-- By Michael Shields
-- Wed Dec 10, 2014 03:28AM EST
-- None



VIENNA, Dec 10 (Reuters) - Part-nationalised Austrian lender Volksbanken AG <OTVVp.VI> and its partners have agreed to sell their Romanian business to Banca Transilvania <ROTLV.BX>, Volksbanken said on Wednesday.

Volksbanken gave no financial details in a statement that said the deal was set to close in the first half of 2015 pending regulatory approval.